===Binomial coefficients===
A simple example of a multidimensional recurrence relation is given by the binomial coefficients formula_35, which count the ways of selecting formula_2 elements out of a set of formula_1 elements.
They can be computed by the recurrence relation
:formula_38
with the base cases formula_39. Using this formula to compute the values of all binomial coefficients generates an infinite array called Pascal&#x27;s triangle. The same values can also be computed directly by a different formula that is not a recurrence, but uses factorials, multiplication and division, not just additions:
:formula_40

The binomial coefficients can also be computed with a uni-dimensional recurrence:
